<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use this pattern to tell users about a change in Tariff classification or Combined Nomenclature codes.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How to design using this pattern</h2>


<div class="govuk-inset-text">
   Do not make any changes to the Tariff notice. It must be an exact copy of the text that’s been provided and must match <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/homepage.html" class="govuk-link">EU legislation</a>.
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Document type</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">Detailed guide</p>


<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Title</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
The title should be ‘[Description] (Tariff notice [number])’.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Body</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">In the first paragraph, link to the relevant <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/homepage.html" class="govuk-link">EU legislation</a>.</p>

<p class="govuk-body">Put one of these sentences after the first paragraph:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
<li>‘This is considered a change in UK practice.’</li>
<li>‘This is not considered a change in UK practice.’</li>
</ul>

<h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Headings and sub-headings</h4>

<p class="govuk-body">
These will normally follow the same pattern.
</p>

